article.headline: Lehigh 67, N.J. Tech 58
article.story: BETHLEHEM, Pa. (AP) -- Marquis Hall had 12 points and eight assists as Lehigh capitalized on 19 turnovers in a 67-58 win over N.J. Tech on Monday. N.J. Tech (0-6) lost despite getting a game-high 20 points from Nesho Milosevic and 16 points from Kraig Peters. Rob Keefer and Matt Szalachowski each added nine points for the Mountain Hawks (3-3). Bryan White had eight points and seven rebounds. Lehigh scored 23 points off turnovers. Prentice Small scored eight points and Zahir Carrington added seven as the Mountain Hawks used a balanced attack, with only Hall scoring in double figures. Lehigh led by three at the half of a game that saw eight lead changes. But they pulled away after the break and held off N.J. Tech despite not making a field goal over the final 5:26.
